## 🧮 SIAM News Feature

**📄 Title:** *Impact of Soil Hydraulic Parameter Variability on Soil Moisture: An Empirical Orthogonal Function Analysis*  
**📍 Publisher:** Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics (SIAM)  
**📅 Published:** February 6, 2025  

**📗 Summary:**  
In this article for *SIAM News*, Kachinga Silwimba distills key findings from his climate modeling research into a concise, practitioner-friendly piece. He highlights how Empirical Orthogonal Function (EOF) analysis can uncover dominant patterns in soil moisture behavior and stresses the importance of soil parameter sensitivity in simulation reliability.

This feature is a valuable read for scientists working at the interface of applied mathematics, geosciences, and environmental modeling.

🔗 [Read the article on SIAM.org](https://www.siam.org/publications/siam-news/articles/impact-of-soil-hydraulic-parameter-variability-on-soil-moisture-an-empirical-orthogonal-function-analysis/)
